{
  "texts": [
    "The observation made on the histoCNN model showed that the classification accuracy is significant both for training and validation with the highest values obtained in both cases are 0.709 and 0.729 respectively.",
    "Similarly, the performance of mammoCNN based on the classification accuracy of the training and validation were observed.",
    "Results obtained were plotted and they showed that only a slight difference exist between the training and validation result, with the value of 0.805 returned for the latter, while 0.802 for the former.",
    "This performance by the participating models of TwinCNN presents a motivation for addressing the multimodal problem.",
    "The history of the loss function values was also monitored, and results collected for graphing as shown in Fig. 10."
  ]
}